This paper is about learning accurate probabilistic models from data, which is a common task in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on binary classifier calibration, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with adjusting the output of a binary classifier to produce calibrated probabilities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
